reviews.text: The reviews speak for themselves ! I would give 0 stars if possible ! RUDE AND UNPROFESSIONAL RECEPTIONIST STAFF! I was left with a urine infection for over a month without being told i had one ! I also had swollen glands asked for an emergancy appointment which i had to BEG for over the phone. One minute they have NO appointments then after begging for 10 minutes I got one (how does that make sense?), got one for 7am and when I got there on the date given with a text to prove it they sent me away saying I was not booked in. Every time there is an issue! even when I do get an appointment i have to wait over 1hour+ to be seen ! total waste of time ! they never send my prescriptions to the chemist on time ! I have been with them for 25 years and have dealt with health complications this past year which they DO NOT care about ! If you are registered here id say RUN now before you end up like me with random health complications which they WILL  NOT tend to! People only give 1+ stars on their reviews here because they obviously are normally healthy and have the one off appointment but I DO NOT RECCOMMED !!! This WAS my family doctor and ALL of my family members have left and I AM MOVING MY DOCTORS TO Chaplin Road GP (BEST IN WEMBLEY). I am also making an official complaint to CQC !!!!
Receptionist and Doctors were friendly, no issues and seemed like a normal medical centre so 5 stars.

in fact i was registered at this gp 8 months ago , but now i moved with my family to the next road  , i found them better more caring , more likely to get appointment when we need it . iam sorry if i had to make official complaint to the CQC about this GP but i've really been left with out any options , although i know any complain to the CQC can be taken very serious, however i still see many negative feedback left by others  i really doubt that reception staff and doctors will be ever improved in this practice

really terrible receptionist , shouting at me on phone, really disgraceful
not enough doctors to get appointment !!
so what this GP doing with the nhs??

Despite being here 30 years I was always happy with dr de Kare he seemed to really help. Everyone here was really good apart from disgusting behavior and appalling treatment from a member of reception. This receptionist is malicious and deliberately effecting my treatment I have complained and am still waiting to see what the outcome will be. I would have given the treatment I have received over the years a 5 star but as of the last few months it’s really become a stressful situation whenever I need to see a dr or get my medication this certain receptionist makes it nearly impossible. I don’t understand how a receptionist can have so much control over who or what a patient needs how is this even legal?
Please re-evaluate certain staff members as they’re driving this once recommendable practice into the ground and it’s sad to see
